# Rails 8 Naming Conventions (Critical)

- Model names: singular, PascalCase (User, Farm, InputCost)
- Table names: plural, snake_case (users, farms, input_costs)
- Controller names: plural, PascalCase (FarmsController, InputCostsController)
- Migration names: descriptive snake_case (create_farms, add_region_to_farms)
- File names: always snake_case matching the class name
- Foreign keys: singular_model_name_id (farm_id, user_id, field_id)
- Join tables: alphabetical order, both plural (fields_input_costs)
- Enums: defined in model, stored as integers in DB, always add a DB index
- Scopes: named with descriptive verb phrases (scope :active, -> { where(active: true) })
